cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Stressed SOTA Datasets"
message: "If you use this collection, please cite it as below and also cite the individual dataset(s) and their original sources."
type: dataset
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-06-17"
license:
  - CC-BY-4.0
  - Apache-2.0
url: "https://github.com/SantanderAI/sota-stressed-datasets"
repository-code: "https://github.com/SantanderAI/sota-stressed-datasets"
abstract: >-
  An open collection of well-known benchmark datasets republished in "stressed"
  form: controlled, documented input degradation (shocks such as noise,
  missingness, ambiguity, formatting changes and contradictions) applied to a
  subset of records, for evaluating the robustness of machine-learning and LLM
  systems. Each dataset is self-contained and attributes both its original
  source and Santander AI Lab.
authors:
  - name: "Santander AI Lab"
keywords:
  - benchmark
  - dataset
  - machine learning
  - robustness
  - LLM
  - data stress testing
references:
  - type: dataset
    title: "Stressed German Credit Dataset (SGCD)"
    version: "SGCD-v0.1"
    authors:
      - name: "Santander AI Lab"
    references:
      - type: dataset
        title: "Statlog (German Credit Data)"
        institution:
          name: "UCI Machine Learning Repository"
        url: "https://archive.ics.uci.edu/dataset/144/statlog+german+credit+data"
